01:59:52.100 --> 01:59:56.270
We incorporated our information gathering efforts, as well as guidelines

01:59:56.270 --> 02:00:01.070
developed by the national association of city transportation officials or

02:00:01.370 --> 02:00:03.830
NATO. So if you hear me say natto, it's referring

02:00:03.830 --> 02:00:06.030
to that organization that developed these guidelines.

02:00:07.700 --> 02:00:11.600
The framework that we're putting forward has three areas, general

02:00:11.630 --> 02:00:12.600
terms and conditions.

02:00:13.400 --> 02:00:15.800
General operations and system design.

02:00:17.570 --> 02:00:19.370
So under general terms and conditions.

02:00:20.830 --> 02:00:22.770
We propose, including just a basic.

02:00:23.700 --> 02:00:25.700
Definition of a bike share system. So what are we

02:00:25.700 --> 02:00:26.230
regulating?

02:00:27.800 --> 02:00:31.670
And building off of the city of Portland's adapting that

02:00:31.670 --> 02:00:34.270
to our context, it could be something like a system

02:00:34.270 --> 02:00:37.230
of bicycles or electric bicycles that is made available for

02:00:37.230 --> 02:00:38.830
rent for general public use.

02:00:39.700 --> 02:00:42.970
Generally for short periods of time to include docs for

02:00:43.030 --> 02:00:44.800
storing bicycles when not in use.

02:00:45.800 --> 02:00:48.500
So that's the kind of parameters that we would be

02:00:48.500 --> 02:00:49.930
setting on what we're regulating.

02:00:51.030 --> 02:00:54.300
We also recommend, including a provision that any bike share

02:00:54.770 --> 02:00:55.030
operator.

02:00:55.700 --> 02:00:58.800
Would have to seek legal permission via a license permit

02:00:58.970 --> 02:01:01.100
or contract or some combination thereof.

02:01:02.000 --> 02:01:06.770
To operate. We are recommended that those be renewed annually.

02:01:07.500 --> 02:01:08.970
And that just means that.

02:01:09.800 --> 02:01:13.000
If the operator is not complying with the, the agreement.

02:01:13.930 --> 02:01:18.000
We have the ability to not renew that in the

02:01:18.000 --> 02:01:18.070
future.

02:01:20.100 --> 02:01:21.570
We also recommend that the city.

02:01:22.570 --> 02:01:24.000
Require the bike share operator.

02:01:25.300 --> 02:01:28.370
To provide indemnity and hold appropriate insurance.

02:01:30.070 --> 02:01:32.930
There's also a provision to clarify that the bike share

02:01:33.230 --> 02:01:35.600
operator will be responsible for any additional costs.

02:01:36.630 --> 02:01:38.770
That might stem from bike share. So that might be

02:01:38.770 --> 02:01:40.970
increased repair or maintenance costs.

02:01:41.800 --> 02:01:43.830
That stem from having bike share in the city.

02:01:46.930 --> 02:01:47.230
Second.

02:01:48.070 --> 02:01:50.930
Under general conditions, we would like the ordinance to spell

02:01:50.930 --> 02:01:52.770
out safety and maintenance requirements.

02:01:54.070 --> 02:01:58.470
So first the operator should comply with local state and

02:01:58.470 --> 02:02:01.600
federal safety standards. For example, the type of equipment that's

02:02:01.600 --> 02:02:03.930
used should meet those basic standards.

02:02:05.030 --> 02:02:10.500
Standards. It's also possible to set a maximum e-bike speed.

02:02:10.830 --> 02:02:13.570
So for example, natto recommends a maximum.

02:02:14.370 --> 02:02:15.470
Speed of 20 miles per hour.

02:02:16.670 --> 02:02:20.300
For a bike share program, but council could consider something

02:02:20.370 --> 02:02:24.000
lower. For example, 15 miles per hour. If they felt

02:02:23.970 --> 02:02:26.700
the 20 miles per hour was not appropriate.

02:02:27.500 --> 02:02:30.000
Finally, there's the possibility to limit the number of bikes

02:02:30.000 --> 02:02:33.430
in the system, or define how regularly these should be

02:02:33.430 --> 02:02:36.570
